msgid ""
"The system dimension ``N_c`` is inferred from ``len(fir_coeffs)``. At "
"each step, the carrier output is the filtered state component ``x[2]``, "
"and the next iterate is computed by :func:`henon_n4_step_inplace`."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.maps.henon_order_n:8 of
msgid ""
"The ``driving`` parameter lets callers override the nonlinear input: when"
" ``driving=None`` the map runs autonomously (``s = x[2]``); when "
"``driving`` is provided the map is forced by that external signal. This "
"is used by the transmitter (self-driven) vs. the receiver (driven by the "
"received signal)."
msgstr ""

